subSubSection.paragraph:
Etymology: Named in honor of the Captain Kidd Pub (Woods Hole), very famous for oceanographers and marine biologists where we have discussed a lot of our zoological and other problems… and made a lot of good friends. The feminine genitive form reflects the gender of "pub" in Spanish, German, Russian and other languages, just as "ship" is feminine (
e.g., Neopilina galatheae
).
